RIYADH: The King Abdulaziz and His Companions Foundation for Giftedness and Creativity signed a memorandum of understanding with Huawei Tech Investment Saudi Arabia Co. to develop the digital skills of Mawhibaâ€™s students and trainers.
	The agreement will train students nominated by Mawhiba on advanced and emerging technologies, granting the institution access to Huawei virtual platforms and their associated educational resources. Mawhiba has selected two training courses for its students and trainers, which will award them the Huawei Certified ICT Associate qualification. The courses provide a comprehensive understanding of public network technologies and design and implement them.